abstract: What happens if your local retail store becomes a showroom for online stores with lower prices?
snippet: What happens if your local retail store becomes a showroom for online stores with lower prices?
lead_paragraph: Lots of people enjoy saving money by shopping online. The prices are often lower, and in many cases there is no sales tax and little or no shipping charge. But while free market forces prevail, there are growing problems with the after-effects of this market shift to Internet sales.

headline.main: Occupy Wall Street? Who Will Occupy Main Street?
